<$fill $name="body">

!! Q: The LLM cannot read or modify a specific tiddler. Why?

The tiddler is likely matched by the protection filter. By default, all tiddlers tagged `sensitive` and all rimir plugin internals (`$:/plugins/rimir/*`) are hidden from the LLM. Check Settings > Protection Filter to see the active filter and adjust it if needed. You can also add per-chat protection via the shield icon.

!! Q: Can I use llm-connect with a single-file wiki (no server)?

Yes. llm-connect is entirely browser-side — it makes direct XHR calls to the LLM provider API from the browser. No TiddlyWiki server is required. You only need a valid API key and a modern browser with CORS support (all major LLM APIs support browser-origin requests).

!! Q: How do I attach a PDF to a conversation?

Use the context filter (paperclip icon in the chat panel). Enter a filter that matches tiddlers with `_canonical_uri` pointing to PDFs, e.g., `[title[My Document.pdf]]`. The file resolver detects the `_canonical_uri`, fetches the file via XHR, base64-encodes it, and sends it to the LLM as a document attachment. Maximum file size is configurable (default 20 MB).

</$fill>
</$transclude>
