<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

llm connect bridges TiddlyWiki with LLM APIs (Claude, OpenAI, Azure OpenAI) directly from the browser. The wiki acts as the orchestrator: sends prompts, receives tool calls, executes them against `$tw.wiki`, and returns results — all without a server.

!! Features

* ''Two modes'' — interactive chat (multi-turn with tools) and one-shot actions (context template → LLM → output target)
* ''Pair editing'' — toolbar button opens an embedded chat panel on any tiddler for collaborative editing with the LLM
* ''Provider adapters'' — Claude, OpenAI, and Azure OpenAI out of the box, extensible adapter interface
* ''Tool system'' — search, read, navigate, create, modify, delete tiddlers; user-defined tools via wikitext
* ''Multimodal context'' — attach PDFs, images, and text tiddlers via a context filter (📎 icon); binaries are base64-encoded and sent inline
* ''Document extraction'' — PDF/DOCX/XLSX files are auto-converted to markdown text (via pdftotext/pandoc/openpyxl) before sending to the LLM — massive token savings vs base64. Extracted text cached per document. Requires runner plugin + server-side tools
* ''Model tier routing'' — assign cost tiers (cheap/default/expensive) to tools; the orchestrator automatically switches models per tool round. Toggle via layers icon in chat header
* ''Context templates'' — wikitext templates that render input from source tiddlers before sending to the LLM
* ''Output targets'' — display only, write to field, create new tiddler, or filter-resolved target
* ''Template precedence'' — tiddler field → prompt template → widget attribute → global default
* ''Debug panel'' — 🐛 icon toggles a live preview of the request payload or the last sent request; base64 data abbreviated
* ''Resizable chat'' — drag panel edges to resize the chat window; drag the history resize handle to adjust the split between history and debug
* ''Tiddler protection'' — restricted wiki proxy hides sensitive tiddlers from all LLM tool execution
* ''Accessible tiddlers panel'' — 👁️ icon shows which tiddlers the LLM can access; drop tiddlers to grant access
* ''Chat pin/save/restore'' — 📌 icon persists a chat to disk; auto-syncs all state; restore after reload
* ''Audit logging'' — write operations execute immediately with an audit log to `$:/temp/rimir/llm-connect/write-log`

!! Prerequisites

* API key for a supported provider (Claude, OpenAI, or Azure OpenAI)
* Modern browser (async/await, XMLHttpRequest)
* ''For document extraction'': runner plugin enabled, plus server-side tools: `pdftotext` (poppler-utils), `pandoc`, `python3-openpyxl`

!! Quick start

# Install the plugin
# Go to Settings and enter your API key
# Open the chat from the page toolbar button
# Click the pair-edit button ({{$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/icon}}) in any tiddler's toolbar for collaborative editing
# Or add action buttons to tiddlers:

```
<$button>
  Summarize
  <$llm-action tiddler=<<currentTiddler>> prompt="Summarize in 3 bullets."/>
</$button>
```

!! Pair editing

Click the pair-edit toolbar button on any tiddler to open an embedded chat panel below the tiddler body. The LLM receives the tiddler's current wikitext as context and can read and write the tiddler using tools. Use it to collaboratively refine content, fix wikitext, or restructure a tiddler — say "apply" and the LLM writes the changes directly.

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">
API keys are stored in wiki tiddlers — visible to anyone with file access. Suitable for personal wikis or server wikis with authentication.
</$fill>
</$transclude>

</$fill>
</$transclude>
