!! Widget: `<$llm-chat>`

|!Attribute |!Description |!Default |
|`chatTiddler` |Tiddler to store conversation messages |required |
|`tiddler` |Source tiddler (sets `currentTiddler` for context) | |
|`systemPrompt` |System prompt text |global config |
|`tools` |Filter for tool tiddlers |none |
|`toolGroup` |Tool group name — restricts active tools to group members |none |
|`contextTemplate` |Context template tiddler title |precedence chain |
|`actionMode` |`yes` — hides message history until first action starts; allows empty send (sends "Go.") |`no` |
|`sendLabel` |Custom label for the send button |`Send` |
|`placeholder` |Custom placeholder text for the textarea |default text |
|`protectionMode` |`allow` (whitelist) or `deny` (blacklist) |global config |
|`allowFilter` |Allow filter (combined with base allow filter) |none |
|`denyFilter` |Deny filter (combined with base deny filter) |none |
|`defaultContext` |Space-separated prefixes for default help context keys (e.g. `rimir/typed tw-gotchas`). Matched keys are pre-selected at widget mount |`tw-gotchas` |

!! Widget: `<$llm-action>`

|!Attribute |!Description |!Default |
|`tiddler` |Source tiddler |none |
|`prompt` |Inline prompt text |none |
|`promptTemplate` |Prompt template tiddler title |none |
|`contextTemplate` |Context template override |precedence chain |
|`context` |Filter for context attachments (text and file tiddlers) |none |
|`outputTarget` |Override template's output target |template value |
|`outputMode` |Override `text` / `markup` |template value |
|`tools` |Filter for tool tiddlers |none (no tools) |
|`toolGroup` |Tool group name — restricts active tools to group members |none |
|`systemPrompt` |Override system prompt |global config |
|`provider` |Provider name (`claude`, `openai`, `azure`) |global config |
|`model` |Model ID override |provider default |
|`protectionMode` |`allow` (whitelist) or `deny` (blacklist) |global config |
|`allowFilter` |Allow filter (combined with base allow filter) |none |
|`denyFilter` |Deny filter (combined with base deny filter) |none |
|`statusTiddler` |Custom tiddler for status text (enables per-instance status) |`$:/temp/rimir/llm-connect/action-status` |
|`resultTiddler` |Custom tiddler for result output (enables per-instance results) |`$:/temp/rimir/llm-connect/action-result` |

!! Context template fields

Tag: `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/context-template`

|!Field |!Values |!Description |
|`template-name` |string |Display name |
|`template-description` |string |Description |
|`output-mode` |`text` / `markup` |How to render output |
|`output-target` |`display` / `field:<name>` / `new-tiddler` / filter |Where response goes |
|`inject-as` |`user-message` / `system-prompt` |How context is injected |
|`output-title-template` |string |Title pattern for new tiddlers (`$(currentTiddler)$` substitution) |
|`output-tags` |string |Tags for new tiddlers |
|`output-fields` |JSON |Additional fields for new tiddlers |

!! Prompt template fields

Tag: `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/prompt`

|!Field |!Description |
|`prompt-name` |Display name |
|`prompt-template` |The prompt text |
|`context-template` |Default context template for this prompt |
|`output-mode` |Default output mode |
|`output-target` |Default output target |

!! Tool definition fields

Tag: `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tool`

|!Field |!Description |
|`tool-name` |Name sent to LLM (e.g. `search_tiddlers`) |
|`tool-description` |Description sent to LLM |
|`tool-schema` |JSON Schema for input parameters |
|`tool-mode` |`read` — render wikitext, return text output. `action` — render + invoke action widgets, return confirmation text (audit logged) |
|`tool-enabled` |`yes` (default) / `no` — disabled tools are excluded from LLM tool lists and cannot be invoked. Use this to keep work-in-progress tools inactive |
|`tool-model-tier` |`cheap` / `default` (default) / `expensive` — cost tier for model tier routing. When tier routing is enabled, the orchestrator switches models based on the highest tier among called tools |
|`tool-category` |Category name for grouping in the tool selector tree (e.g. `core`, `pdf`) |

!! Per-chat tool selection

Each chat instance stores its active tools in the `llm-active-tools` field on its chat tiddler (a TiddlyWiki title list). Click the wrench icon in the chat header to open the tool selector:

* ''All / None'' — quick select/deselect all tools
* ''Group buttons'' — apply a tool group preset (replaces current selection)
* ''Checkboxes'' — toggle individual tools; hover for description

When `llm-active-tools` is not set, all built-in (shadow) tools are used by default. On first open, the selector initializes with only `tool-category: core` tools checked. Setups that pre-populate `llm-active-tools` and set `llm-tools-init: yes` on the chat tiddler bypass this default. The dropdown closes automatically when clicking outside it.

The orchestrator enforces tool selection at execution time — even if the LLM attempts to call a tool not in the active set, the call is rejected with an error message.

!! Tool groups

Tag: `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tool-group`

|!Field |!Description |
|`group-name` |Display name shown in the tool selector |
|`group-description` |Tooltip text when hovering the group button |
|`group-tools` |TiddlyWiki title list of tool tiddler titles included in this group |

Groups are presets — clicking a group button in the tool selector replaces the chat's active tools with the group's tool set. Create and manage groups in Settings > Tool Groups.

A tool is considered ''complete'' when `tool-name`, `tool-schema`, and `text` (body) are all non-empty. Incomplete tools cannot be activated or cloned from the settings UI.

!! Built-in tools

|!Tool name |!Mode |!Description |
|`search_tiddlers` |`read` |Run a filter and return matching titles with tags |
|`get_tiddler` |`read` |Read a tiddler's fields and text |
|`set_field` |`action` |Set a field value on an existing tiddler |
|`create_tiddler` |`action` |Create a new tiddler. `title` (exact, fails if exists) or `basetitle` (auto-numbered if taken, returns actual title). Auto-added to protection filter |
|`delete_tiddler` |`action` |Delete a tiddler |
|`navigate_to_tiddler` |`action` |Open a tiddler in the story river so the user can see it |
|`wikitext_render` |`read` |Render wikitext and return the text output |
|`attach_document` |`action` |Attach a binary file (PDF, DOCX, XLSX, image) to the conversation. Queues the document for injection; if extraction is enabled, PDF/DOCX/XLSX are sent as markdown text instead of base64 |
|`pdf_store_summary` |`action` |Store a structured summary linked to a parent document. Creates a summary tiddler with metadata |

!! Artifact fields

Derived tiddlers created by llm-connect carry lifecycle fields for cascade cleanup (requires file-upload plugin):

|!Tiddler pattern |!`_artifact_type` |!Description |
|`<title>.extracted` |`extraction` |Cached markdown text extraction from a binary document |
|`<title>.extracted/<img>` |`extraction-image` |Extracted image from a PDF (has `_canonical_uri` to `files/_derived/`) |
|`<title>.summaries/<model>-<ts>` |`summary` |LLM-generated summary of a document |

All carry `_artifact_source` pointing to the parent file tiddler. When the parent is deleted/renamed (via file-upload hooks), artifacts are automatically cascaded.

Action-mode tools (`set_field`, `create_tiddler`, `delete_tiddler`, `navigate_to_tiddler`) execute immediately and append an entry to the audit log at `$:/temp/rimir/llm-connect/write-log`.

!! Variables in tool wikitext

The property names from `tool-schema` become widget variables inside the tool's text body. For example, a schema with `"properties": {"title": ..., "filter": ...}` makes `<<title>>` and `<<filter>>` available.

|!Schema property type |!Variable value |
|`string` |The string as-is |
|`number` |String representation |
|`object` |JSON-serialized string |

Variables for parameters the LLM did not provide resolve to empty string.

Additionally, the tool executor injects these built-in context variables (available to all tools):

|!Variable |!Description |
|`<<__timestamp>>` |Current time in TW format (`YYYYMMDDHHMMSSMMM`) |
|`<<__provider>>` |Active provider name (e.g. `claude`) |
|`<<__model>>` |Active model ID (e.g. `claude-opus-4-20250514`) |

!! Custom tools

Create custom tools from the Settings > Tools panel using ''Create new tool'' or ''Clone'' (copy icon on any existing tool). Clones start disabled (`tool-enabled: no`) so you can edit them before activation.

Alternatively, create a tool tiddler manually — tag it `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tool` with the fields above. The tiddler body contains wikitext that receives LLM inputs as variables:

```
title: $:/my-tools/get-tagged
tags: $:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tool
tool-name: get_tagged_tiddlers
tool-description: Get all tiddlers with a specific tag
tool-schema: {"type":"object","properties":{"tag":{"type":"string"}},"required":["tag"]}
tool-mode: read
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

<$list filter="[tag<tag>]" variable="item">
<$text text=<<item>>/>
</$list>
```

!! Debug panel system

The debug button (🐛) in the bottom toolbar opens a dropdown menu listing all available inspection panels. Click a panel name to open it between the textarea and the toolbar. Click again to close. The panel system is extensible — any plugin can register panels via the tag `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/debug-panel`.

!!! Built-in panels

* ''Request Preview'' — live preview of what will be sent: provider, model, system prompt, messages, pending input, context, tools, protection. Updates as you type.
* ''Last Request Sent'' — raw JSON request body from the last API call. Base64 abbreviated.
* ''Last Response'' — raw JSON response from the last API call. Base64 abbreviated.
* ''Accessible Tiddlers'' — scrollable list of tiddlers the LLM can access based on the active protection filter. Supports drag-and-drop to add/remove tiddlers from the filter.
* ''Logging'' — timestamped debug log of send/request/response/tool execution/tier routing/errors. In-memory only (cleared on reload). Clear button to reset.
* ''Active Tools (int. data)'' — shows the resolved active tool set with name, category, and model tier. Reflects the actual tools the LLM receives (default set before first tool selector click, explicit set after).

!!! Tool-call display (tristate)

The ''No Tool-Calls'' / ''Brief Tool-Calls'' / ''Detailed Tool-Calls'' entry cycles through three display modes for tool-call messages in the chat history:

* ''No Tool-Calls'' (default) — tool messages hidden. An animated `...` indicator appears while tools are executing in the background.
* ''Brief Tool-Calls'' — collapsed one-line summaries visible. Click individual messages to expand.
* ''Detailed Tool-Calls'' — all tool messages fully expanded.

!!! Wikitext panels (extensibility)

Tag a tiddler with `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/debug-panel` and set these fields:

|!Field |!Description |
|`panel-name` |Display name in the menu |
|`panel-icon` |Emoji or icon reference |
|`panel-order` |Numeric sort order (lower = higher in menu) |

The tiddler body is wikitext, rendered with `<<chatTiddler>>` variable available. Example: the ''Help Context (int. data)'' panel is shipped by the llm-help plugin and shows the active help context keys.

!! Token estimate

The toolbar header shows an approximate token count: `~3.2k tok (1.8k in / 1.4k out)`. This is a rough estimate using ~4 characters per token. "In" counts assistant message text, "out" counts user messages, context, and tool results. Base64 image/document data is excluded. Updates after each message exchange.

!! Tools panel (ViewTemplate)

The tools panel (`$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/ui/tools-panel`) is a ViewTemplate element that renders below the tiddler body. It dispatches to matching ''recipes'' — each recipe defines which tiddlers it applies to and what UI to show.

!!! Recipe tiddler fields

Tag: `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tw-recipe`

|!Field |!Description |
|`match-filter` |TiddlyWiki filter evaluated against `currentTiddler`. If the filter returns any result, the recipe's UI renders |
|`recipe-name` |Display name |
|`recipe-order` |Numeric sort order (lower = higher priority) |

The tiddler body contains the recipe's wikitext UI, which typically includes `<$llm-action>` invocations with tool-use.

!!! Adding a new recipe

Create a tiddler tagged `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tw-recipe` with a `match-filter` and wikitext body. Example — a recipe that shows for all tiddlers tagged "report":

```
tags: $:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tw-recipe
match-filter: [all[current]tag[report]]
recipe-name: Summarize Report
recipe-order: 200
```

!!! Built-in recipes

|!Recipe |!Match filter |!Description |
|PDF Summary |`[all[current]has[_canonical_uri]type[application/pdf]]` |Opens a floating chat panel pre-configured for PDF summarization. Uses `<$llm-chat>` with `pdf-tools` tool group, PDF context, and summary system prompt. Creates summary tiddler via `pdf_store_summary` tool |

Recipe panels reuse the full `<$llm-chat>` widget, giving access to model selection, tool management, debug panel, protection filters, and context filters — the same capabilities as the global chat panel.

!!! `pdf_store_summary` tool

Creates a summary tiddler linked to a parent PDF. Called by the LLM during PDF summarization.

|!Parameter |!Type |!Required |!Description |
|`parent_title` |string |yes |Title of the PDF tiddler being summarized |
|`summary` |string |yes |Summary content in wikitext format |
|`additional_requirements` |string |no |Extra user instructions |

Summary tiddler conventions:

* Title: `<parent>.summaries/<model>-<timestamp>` (dot-separated to avoid filesystem conflicts when parent ends in a file extension)
* Tag: `llm-summary`
* Fields: `parent`, `summary-model`, `summary-timestamp`, `additional-requirements`

!! Bundled context templates

|!Template |!Tiddler |!Description |
|Pair editing |`$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/context-templates/pair-edit` |Sends the tiddler's raw wikitext for collaborative editing; output-mode `markup`, inject-as `user-message` |

