!! Accessible tiddlers panel

The 👁️ button in the chat header toggles a scrollable list of all tiddler titles the LLM can currently access. The list is computed from the combined protection filter (base + widget attributes + per-chat).

''Drag-and-drop'' — drop a tiddler onto the panel to grant the LLM access:

* ''Allow mode'' — appends `[[title]]` to the per-chat allow filter
* ''Deny mode'' — appends `-[[title]]` to the per-chat deny filter (exempts it from the blacklist)

Titles are clickable links (navigates to tiddler). The list refreshes when protection mode or filters change.

!! Per-chat fields

The following fields on each chat tiddler control per-chat behaviour. They are managed by the chat UI — not config tiddlers.

|!Field |!Description |
|`llm-active-tools` |TiddlyWiki title list of active tool tiddlers (managed by wrench icon) |
|`llm-context-filter` |TiddlyWiki filter expression for context attachments (managed by 📎 icon). Results are classified as text or file tiddlers and included in the first message |
|`llm-protection-mode` |Protection mode override for this chat — `allow` or `deny` (managed by shield icon dropdown). Switching modes auto-negates the per-chat filter |
|`llm-allow-filter` |Additional allow filter for this chat (managed by shield icon). Combined with widget attribute and base allow filter |
|`llm-deny-filter` |Additional deny filter for this chat (managed by shield icon). Combined with widget attribute and base deny filter |
|`llm-help-context` |Space-separated list of active llm-help context keys (managed by ? icon). Each chat has its own context — synced to the global tiddler before tool execution |
|`llm-pinned-save` |`"yes"` when chat is pinned (auto-syncing to saved tiddler). Managed by 📌 icon |

!! Help context selector

The ? icon in the chat header allows toggling llm-help context keys directly from the chat. This button is only visible when the `$:/plugins/rimir/llm-help` plugin is installed and at least one context key exists.

Context is stored per-chat on the `llm-help-context` field (like tool selection). When the LLM executes tools, the chat's context is synced to the global `$:/temp/rimir/llm-help/active-context` tiddler so the `llm_help` tool picks it up. Both popup state and context values are independent across global chat, pair-edit panels, and appify chat.

* ''All'' / ''None'' — enable or clear all context keys
* ''Context groups'' — predefined sets of context keys, configured via tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/context-group`

Context group tiddlers use the same pattern as tool groups:

|!Field |!Description |
|`group-name` |Display name for the group button |
|`group-contexts` |Space-separated list of context keys to activate |
|`group-description` |Tooltip text |

The selector writes to the chat tiddler's `llm-help-context` field — each chat has independent context. Before tool execution, the chat's context is synced to the global `$:/temp/rimir/llm-help/active-context` tiddler so the `llm_help` tool picks it up.

!! Shared chat toolbar

The chat header toolbar (pin, export/import, tool selector, context selector) is defined once in `$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/ui/chat-toolbar` and imported by all chat panel templates. Two procedures are available:

* `<<llm-chat-toolbar-left "Label">>` — renders the pin button and label
* `<<llm-chat-toolbar-actions "chatTiddler">>` — renders export/import buttons, tier routing toggle, tool selector, and context selector
* `<<llm-tier-toggle>>` — layers icon: hover shows tier config (cheap/default/expensive models), click toggles `$:/config/rimir/llm-connect/tier-routing-enabled`. Icon highlights in primary color when active

External plugins (e.g. appify) can import `chat-toolbar` to get the full toolbar without duplicating markup.

!! Chat export/import

The ↑ (export) and ↓ (import) arrow buttons in the chat header allow transferring conversations between browser sessions, devices, or users.

''Export'' copies a JSON snapshot of the entire chat to the clipboard — messages, provider, model, tool selection, protection mode/filters, context filter, and injection state. The status bar confirms success with a message count.

''Import'' reads JSON from the clipboard and restores the chat. If the browser blocks clipboard read access, a paste dialog appears as fallback. Importing overwrites the current chat state (clear first if you want to preserve it).

The JSON format includes a `version` field for forward compatibility and an `exported` timestamp.

!! Chat pin/save/restore

The 📌 icon at the top-right of the chat container pins the current chat to persist it to disk. Chat tiddlers use `$:/temp/` paths which are lost on browser reload — pinning creates a persistent copy at `$:/saved-chats/rimir/llm-connect/<context-slug>`.

Each widget context (global chat, chat view, each pair-edit tiddler) has one save slot. Pinned chats auto-sync ''all'' state on every change: messages, protection mode/filters, tool selection, context filter, and injection flags.

|!Pin state |!Click action |
|Not pinned, no save |Pin (create save) |
|Not pinned, has save, chat empty |Restore saved chat |
|Not pinned, has save, chat has messages |Context menu: "Save current" / "Restore saved" |
|Pinned |Unpin (stop syncing; save remains) |

Saved tiddler fields include `llm-context-injected`, `llm-attachments-injected`, and `llm-system-prompt-override` to correctly restore widget-internal state and prevent duplicate context injection.

!! Source tiddler auto-access

When the `tiddler` attribute is set (e.g. pair-edit mode), the source tiddler is automatically added to the allow filter (or exempted from the deny filter). This ensures the LLM can always read and modify the tiddler it is pair-editing.

